  "title": "Sales Manager",
  "description": "<p>·        \nDevelop and execute sales strategies to grow\nbusiness in marine engineering, ship repair, and offshore sectors.</p><p>·        \nIdentify new clients, projects, and business\nopportunities within the marine industry.</p><p>·        \nHandle the full sales cycle—from lead\ngeneration, enquiry handling, proposal submission, to deal closure.</p><p>·        \nBuild and maintain strong relationships with\nshipowners, shipyards, managers, and marine contractors.</p><p>·        \nConduct client meetings, vessel visits, and\npresentations to understand technical requirements.</p><p>·        \nCoordinate with engineering and operations teams\nto prepare quotations, costings, and scope of work.</p><p>·        \nReview RFQs and ensure accurate pricing,\ntimelines, and technical compliance.</p><p>·        \nFollow up on ongoing quotations, negotiate\nterms, and secure contracts.</p><p>·        \nMonitor project execution to ensure client\nsatisfaction and timely delivery.</p><p>·        \nTrack sales performance, prepare monthly\nreports, and update management on progress.</p><p>·        \nParticipate in marine exhibitions, trade shows,\nand industry networking events.</p><p>·        \nPromote company services and capabilities\nthrough presentations and marketing materials.</p><p>·        \nSupport timely invoice submission and follow up\nfor payment collection.</p><p>·        \nAchieve sales targets and contribute to company\nrevenue growth.</p><p>·        \nMaintain CRM records, client databases, and\nsales documentation.</p>",
